<br>
I will agree with some but argue others..<br>
<br>
Run 3, Agree - you probably save 2-3 full hits while pulling dungeon mobs back to the groups. 4-5 if you get stunned often.<br>
<br>
3 more to burn, if you have any stats that are seriously lacking maybe put them there - or Regen.  Stat boosts always seem to pay off, even if only a little.<br>
<br>
Combat Stability 3:  Here's why.  2,5,10% dmg reduction - always and forever.  In the course of a night of fighting, thats 10% less overall dammage that your cleric has to heal!  With multiple mobs, it's that much less damage per mob on you thus exponentially more valuable.  So durability will give you a bigger gas tank, but stabilty will give you more miles per gallon.<br>
<br>
Combat Agility 3:  Again, it's giving you more duration for your given hitpoints.  I guess typical tank thinking is &quot;Ug, my HP's are bigger than You's!&quot; - but if the hitpoints you do have last longer isnt that most likely better?  Not unlike AC vs HP's?  I'd rather give up some hitpoints to have more AC and take less dammage.<br>
<br>
Natural Durability 3:  Lastly I'm thinking that with all of the reduction in dammage the increased buffer is a valuable bonus.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now a thought on the regen - if you did the first 3 regen, I guess thats ok, and it fits in with the improved miles per gallon concept I'm using.  Then if you did the next 3 regen points your up to 6 / tick.  In long battles as the main tank this may have a decent pay off - not unlike the other damage reduction skills.<br>
<br>
Mind you I nearly always am the main tank - and as such I put emphasis on taking the dammage and living long enough for the other dammage doers to do their jobs.<br>
<br>
<br>
Just my two copper - I'd be interested to hear your thoughts.<br>
<br>
-Huzbub<br>
